    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Wood of the species Quercus robur, having a coarse but straight grain that is usually a rich brown color. Flat sawn timber has a distinctive figuring while radial cut lumber has silver grain lines. The wood has a high gallic acid content that will corrode iron and other contacting metals. English oak is widely used in furniture, paneling, railway sleepers, cabinet, musical instruments, and ship building.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
